---
import BaseLayout from "@/layouts/BaseLayout.astro";
---

<BaseLayout title="Skewed - Francois Laberge" favicon="ðŸ§±">
  <div class="space-y-8 max-w-2xl">
    <div>
      <a
        href="/projects"
        class="text-sm text-muted-foreground hover:text-foreground transition-colors"
      >
        &larr; Back to Projects
      </a>
    </div>

    <div class="space-y-1">
      <p class="text-xs text-muted-foreground uppercase tracking-wide">October 2023</p>
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-bold tracking-tight">Skewed</h1>
      <p class="text-muted-foreground">
        An easy to use 3D engine that renders SVG, written in TypeScript.
      </p>
    </div>

    <div class="prose dark:prose-invert max-w-none space-y-4">
      <p>
        Skewed is a TypeScript-based 3D engine that renders SVG. It:
      </p>
      <ul>
        <li>Facilitates interactive explanations needing neat 3D visuals.</li>
        <li>Outputs pristine SVG for additional manipulation in Figma.</li>
        <li>Uses a React renderer with a custom reconciler.</li>
        <li>Aiming for exceptionally clean code, though it's a work in progress.</li>
      </ul>

      <p>
        Here's a <a href="https://vgyf3c.csb.app/" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">live demo</a>.
        Check it out on GitHub: <a href="https://github.com/seflless/skewed" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">github.com/seflless/skewed</a>.
      </p>

      <div class="space-y-6">
        <img
          src="/projects/skewed/light-spinning-around-shapes.gif"
          alt="Light spinning around 3D shapes rendered as SVG"
          class="rounded-lg w-full"
          width="640"
          height="478"
        />
        <img
          src="/projects/skewed/octopus.gif"
          alt="3D octopus rendered as SVG"
          class="rounded-lg w-full"
          width="640"
          height="478"
        />
        <img
          src="/projects/skewed/rotating-text.gif"
          alt="Rotating 3D text rendered as SVG"
          class="rounded-lg w-full"
          width="640"
          height="478"
        />
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>
